Manage Consent

We use cookies and other similar technologies, including cookies provided by analytics, advertising, and other third-party providers. These cookies may record what pages you visit and other similar activity on our website, including what videos on our website you may watch. By continuing to browse our website, you consent to such recording and the disclosure of these activities on our website to these third-parties and our use of your personal information as further described in our Privacy Policy (https://precisefp.com/privacy-policy). For more information about the specific cookies we use on our website and your choices regarding such recording, please visit our Cookie Policy and Settings (https://precisefp.com/coookie-settings).

Frequently asked questions
--------------------------

##### How long is the trial?

Your trial will last 14 days. After your trial ends, your account will activate automatically and your monthly subscription will begin. You can cancel your trial at any moment.

##### Are there any limitations with the trial?

There are no limitations with the trial. Your account is a fully functioning account, complete with any integrations that you choose to activate.

##### How do I reach support with questions?

Support help is available Mon – Fri, 9:00 a.m. to 6:00 p.m. EST. You can chat with us live from our website, or within PreciseFP itself. We strive to provide instant responses, but typically will respond in less than 5 minutes (if there happens to be a delay). We find chat to be extremely powerful and efficient as it allows us to share links and screen captures; something that is not possible over the phone.

##### What is the difference between a user and a team?

A user is someone that logs into the application. A user can be an advisor, assistant, paraplanner, compliance officer, office administrator, etc. There is no limit to the number of Users you can have on your monthly subscription, though beyond the first User these come at an additional cost.

A team is where your clients and prospects will reside. Your account comes with one team but if you need to split your clients and prospects by department, location, office, etc, then you should create additional teams. Users assigned to a team are only able to access clients and prospects of that team.

##### Can I add/remove users or teams whenever I want?

Yes. You are able to add and remove users, teams, clients, and prospects at any moment. Your monthly subscription price will automatically update whenever you add or remove a user, a team, a client or a prospect.

##### Do you offer discounts?

We do not offer discounts at the moment. If you need more time to evaluate the application during your trial, feel free to reach out to us for an extension.
